entry.title: Experiment 4.5: Agents=1k; randomJumpParameter=1;believe=0,15;iterations=150
entry.content:
The simulation was set to run for 300 generations, but after around 140 generations the time of each generation became very long (probably because challenges started to multiply - this is something to attend in the future). But, the average degree at that time was already above 10 (something that I was not being able to achieve )

Analyses

Analysis 4.5/1: average benefit dynamics: looks somewhat more interesting, at least the benefit accumulation per time is not constant, but also not something expected

Analysis 4.5/2: challenge distribution: shows that with the higher degree the challenge propagation becomes more normally distributed. Completely logical, but points to the need of further analyses..

entry.title: Experiment 4/2: 3k Agents; randomJumpParameter 99
entry.content:
Changes to the code just before:

  • weightHistory parameter on every link, allowing to get all changes link weights with timestamps of events;
  • bug fix: corrected the mess with reciprocal links;
  • bug fix: links to generator of diversity were not set to 1 initially;
  • bug fix: got rid of testNG tests in favor of JUnit: some important tests were not passing because of that.

Running 3000 agents with randomJumpParameter equal to 99 for a quick test of the refreshed codebase.

Analyses

Analysis 4.2/1: benefit increase

Nothing different from previous attemps - the benefit increase per unit of time is flat
